(
<emphasis id="1CC391076FCC072E9A511C8E1F56B705" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">E-H</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C8CC91411126A7CF32B58F31CA9E2685" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="description">
<paragraph id="083D313649F85CFAEFCB8C1F37CD1CA2" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Culture characteristics.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C38C8EA6514779F93CEDA3DA29B1C93A" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="D8A0B356B21EEF0B65A7DAE423D6AE31" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Cultures</emphasis>
are white, growing up to 4 cm in diam. with irregular margin after 3 days, covering the 9 cm Petri dish after 6 days, becoming vinaceous buff to hazel after 7-10 days. In reverse, the cultures are the same as the upper colour after 3 days, becoming isabelline to umber after 7-10 days. 
<emphasis id="04D6E7FC25B943FABE1995B031008264" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Colonies</emphasis>
are felty with a heterogeneous texture, lacking aerial mycelium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F23190A92DE8CF3A9C4B6FBF08314CC0" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="habitat">
